</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF516AEEFCF9977F1B06BAD7" blockId="170.[773,1367,294,722]" pageId="170" pageNumber="932">
Subgenus Pyzonix; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF516AEEFBF2977F1A83BA75" baseAuthorityName="Le Conte" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[1038,1155,294,327]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="932" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lucifugus">lucifugus</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF516AEEFCFA97141DDBBA5C" authorityName="Miller &amp; G. M. Allen" authorityYear="1928" box="[774,987,333,366]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="932" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="fortidens">Myotis fortidens</taxonomicName>
was originally described as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF516AEEFBE6972C1AC3BAA4" baseAuthorityName="Le Conte" baseAuthorityYear="1831" box="[1050,1219,373,406]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="170" pageNumber="938" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lucifugus">M. lucifugus</taxonomicName>
and later raised to a distinct species based on morphology. Two subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
